headline: Crypto Lender BlockFills Suspends Client Withdrawals
summary: BlockFills, a crypto lending and trading firm for institutional investors, has suspended customer withdrawals in light of the recent crypto plunge.  The Chicago-based company, backed by Susquehanna Private Equity Investments and the venture arm of Chicago Mercantile Exchange owner CME Group, decided to temporarily suspend client deposits and withdrawals last week when bitcoin fell as low as $60,000 before paring losses.

headline: Jobs Report: Strong Hiring May Be Overstated; S&P 500 Wavers
summary: The January jobs report showed stronger hiring in January as the unemployment rate dipped.  The S&P 500 rallied as markets weighed the implications for Federal Reserve policy and economic growth.  The report comes two weeks after the Federal Reserve upgraded the labor market's condition to stable, but that consensus had begun to look fragile after data on Tuesday showed weaker-than-expected wage growth and surprisingly soft retail sales.

headline: Traders Scale Back Rate-Cut Bets...A Little
summary: After a solid jobs report, traders still think that there’s a good chance the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates by the start of summer.  Interest-rate futures on Wednesday morning implied a roughly 49% chance the Fed will cut rates by 0.25 percentage point at or before its June 16-17 meeting, according to CME Group.  The chances of more than one cut fell by a corresponding amount.
